Michaels Stores' Sales Rise
For the fourth quarter ended Feb. 2, Michaels said sales
rose 15%, to $144.2 million from $125.5 million.
Comparable-store sales rose 13% over the fourth quarter a
year ago.
   For all of fiscal 1991, Michaels said sales increased 15%
to $410.9 million from $357 million for the same 52 weeks
last year. For the year, comparable-store sales rose 9.1%.
The company's fiscal 1990 covered a 53-week period, which
included a fifth week in December; it said the sales
comparisons reflect comparable weekly periods.